{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":970,"text":"I am a plant geneticist."},{"time":3292,"text":"I study genes that make plants\nresistant to disease"},{"time":6867,"text":"and tolerant of stress."},{"time":9189,"text":"In recent years,"},{"time":11465,"text":"millions of people around the world\nhave come to believe"},{"time":14367,"text":"that there's something sinister\nabout genetic modification."},{"time":18500,"text":"Today, I am going to provide\na different perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24003,"text":"First, let me introduce my husband, Raoul."},{"time":26569,"text":"He's an organic farmer."},{"time":29192,"text":"On his farm, he plants\na variety of different crops."},{"time":33140,"text":"This is one of the many\necological farming practices"},{"time":36181,"text":"he uses to keep his farm healthy."},{"time":39664,"text":"Imagine some of the reactions we get:"},{"time":42822,"text":"\"Really? An organic farmer\nand a plant geneticist?"},{"time":46398,"text":"Can you agree on anything?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":49439,"text":"Well, we can, and it's not difficult,\nbecause we have the same goal."},{"time":54415,"text":"We want to help nourish\nthe growing population"},{"time":57543,"text":"without further destroying\nthe environment."},{"time":60283,"text":"I believe this is the greatest\nchallenge of our time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65066,"text":"Now, genetic modification is not new;"},{"time":69199,"text":"virtually everything we eat\nhas been genetically modified"},{"time":73169,"text":"in some manner."},{"time":75264,"text":"Let me give you a few examples."},{"time":78376,"text":"On the left is an image"},{"time":80657,"text":"of the ancient ancestor of modern corn."},{"time":85208,"text":"You see a single roll of grain\nthat's covered in a hard case."},{"time":89109,"text":"Unless you have a hammer,"},{"time":91640,"text":"teosinte isn't good for making tortillas."},{"time":96655,"text":"Now, take a look at\nthe ancient ancestor of banana."},{"time":101310,"text":"You can see the large seeds."},{"time":103064,"text":"And unappetizing brussel sprouts,"},{"time":106500,"text":"and eggplant, so beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110122,"text":"Now, to create these varieties,"},{"time":112305,"text":"breeders have used many different\ngenetic techniques over the years."},{"time":115489,"text":"Some of them are quite creative,"},{"time":117053,"text":"like mixing two different species together"},{"time":119607,"text":"using a process called grafting"},{"time":121720,"text":"to create this variety\nthat's half tomato and half potato."},{"time":127525,"text":"Breeders have also used\nother types of genetic techniques,"},{"time":132076,"text":"such as random mutagenesis,"},{"time":134119,"text":"which induces uncharacterized mutations"},{"time":137509,"text":"into the plants."},{"time":139808,"text":"The rice in the cereal\nthat many of us fed our babies"},{"time":144134,"text":"was developed using this approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147957,"text":"Now, today, breeders have\neven more options to choose from."},{"time":151626,"text":"Some of them are extraordinarily precise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155364,"text":"I want to give you a couple examples\nfrom my own work."},{"time":159172,"text":"I work on rice, which is a staple food\nfor more than half the world's people."},{"time":165047,"text":"Each year, 40 percent\nof the potential harvest"},{"time":168181,"text":"is lost to pest and disease."},{"time":171037,"text":"For this reason,\nfarmers plant rice varieties"},{"time":174167,"text":"that carry genes for resistance."},{"time":177023,"text":"This approach has been used\nfor nearly 100 years."},{"time":180761,"text":"Yet, when I started graduate school,"},{"time":183942,"text":"no one knew what these genes were."},{"time":186195,"text":"It wasn't until the 1990s\nthat scientists finally uncovered"},{"time":191280,"text":"the genetic basis of resistance."},{"time":194414,"text":"In my laboratory, we isolated a gene\nfor immunity to a very serious"},{"time":199174,"text":"bacterial disease in Asia and Africa."},{"time":201937,"text":"We found we could engineer the gene\ninto a conventional rice variety"},{"time":207277,"text":"that's normally susceptible,"},{"time":209088,"text":"and you can see the two leaves\non the bottom here"},{"time":211526,"text":"are highly resistant to infection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214499,"text":"Now, the same month\nthat my laboratory published"},{"time":217888,"text":"our discovery on the rice immunity gene,"},{"time":220675,"text":"my friend and colleague Dave Mackill\nstopped by my office."},{"time":224274,"text":"He said, \"Seventy million rice farmers\nare having trouble growing rice.\""},{"time":232864,"text":"That's because their fields are flooded,"},{"time":235651,"text":"and these rice farmers are living\non less than two dollars a day."},{"time":240272,"text":"Although rice grows well\nin standing water,"},{"time":243824,"text":"most rice varieties will die\nif they're submerged"},{"time":246634,"text":"for more than three days."},{"time":248932,"text":"Flooding is expected\nto be increasingly problematic"},{"time":252253,"text":"as the climate changes."},{"time":255062,"text":"He told me that his graduate student\nKenong Xu and himself"},{"time":259497,"text":"were studying an ancient variety of rice\nthat had an amazing property."},{"time":264466,"text":"It could withstand two weeks\nof complete submergence."},{"time":270178,"text":"He asked if I would be willing\nto help them isolate this gene."},{"time":275448,"text":"I said yes -- I was very excited,\nbecause I knew if we were successful,"},{"time":279999,"text":"we could potentially help\nmillions of farmers grow rice"},{"time":283993,"text":"even when their fields were flooded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287453,"text":"Kenong spent 10 years\nlooking for this gene."},{"time":291516,"text":"Then one day, he said,"},{"time":293513,"text":"\"Come look at this experiment.\nYou've got to see it.\""},{"time":297135,"text":"I went to the greenhouse and I saw"},{"time":298992,"text":"that the conventional variety\nthat was flooded for 18 days had died,"},{"time":304292,"text":"but the rice variety that we\nhad genetically engineered"},{"time":307955,"text":"with a new gene we had discovered,\ncalled Sub1, was alive."},{"time":312459,"text":"Kenong and I were amazed and excited"},{"time":314944,"text":"that a single gene could have\nthis dramatic effect."},{"time":318775,"text":"But this is just a greenhouse experiment."},{"time":322417,"text":"Would this work in the field?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":325783,"text":"Now, I'm going to show you\na four-month time lapse video"},{"time":328523,"text":"taken at the International\nRice Research Institute."},{"time":331565,"text":"Breeders there developed\na rice variety carrying the Sub1 gene"},{"time":336590,"text":"using another genetic technique\ncalled precision breeding."},{"time":340226,"text":"On the left, you can see the Sub1 variety,"},{"time":342826,"text":"and on the right\nis the conventional variety."},{"time":346471,"text":"Both varieties do very well at first,"},{"time":348933,"text":"but then the field is flooded for 17 days."},{"time":352346,"text":"You can see the Sub1 variety does great."},{"time":355271,"text":"In fact, it produces\nthree and a half times more grain"},{"time":360124,"text":"than the conventional variety."},{"time":363468,"text":"I love this video"},{"time":365465,"text":"because it shows the power\nof plant genetics to help farmers."},{"time":369760,"text":"Last year, with the help\nof the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation,"},{"time":373150,"text":"three and a half million farmers\ngrew Sub1 rice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377260,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":381439,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385168,"text":"Now, many people don't mind\ngenetic modification"},{"time":389310,"text":"when it comes to moving rice genes around,"},{"time":392050,"text":"rice genes in rice plants,"},{"time":393397,"text":"or even when it comes\nto mixing species together"},{"time":396787,"text":"through grafting or random mutagenesis."},{"time":401036,"text":"But when it comes to taking genes\nfrom viruses and bacteria"},{"time":406214,"text":"and putting them into plants,"},{"time":408002,"text":"a lot of people say, \"Yuck.\""},{"time":411299,"text":"Why would you do that?"},{"time":413458,"text":"The reason is that sometimes\nit's the cheapest, safest,"},{"time":416221,"text":"and most effective technology"},{"time":419333,"text":"for enhancing food security\nand advancing sustainable agriculture."},{"time":424627,"text":"I'm going to give you three examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427668,"text":"First, take a look at papaya.\nIt's delicious, right?"},{"time":430780,"text":"But now, look at this papaya."},{"time":433287,"text":"This papaya is infected\nwith papaya ringspot virus."},{"time":437490,"text":"In the 1950s, this virus\nnearly wiped out the entire production"},{"time":443248,"text":"of papaya on the island of Oahu in Hawaii."},{"time":449169,"text":"Many people thought\nthat the Hawaiian papaya was doomed,"},{"time":453465,"text":"but then, a local Hawaiian,"},{"time":456529,"text":"a plant pathologist\nnamed Dennis Gonsalves,"},{"time":459200,"text":"decided to try to fight this disease\nusing genetic engineering."},{"time":463631,"text":"He took a snippet of viral DNA\nand he inserted it"},{"time":467299,"text":"into the papaya genome."},{"time":469412,"text":"This is kind of like a human\ngetting a vaccination."},{"time":472686,"text":"Now, take a look at his field trial."},{"time":475217,"text":"You can see the genetically\nengineered papaya in the center."},{"time":478839,"text":"It's immune to infection."},{"time":481022,"text":"The conventional papaya around the outside\nis severely infected with the virus."},{"time":486650,"text":"Dennis' pioneering work is credited\nwith rescuing the papaya industry."},{"time":493369,"text":"Today, 20 years later, there's still no\nother method to control this disease."},{"time":498134,"text":"There's no organic method.\nThere's no conventional method."},{"time":501338,"text":"Eighty percent of Hawaiian papaya\nis genetically engineered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505588,"text":"Now, some of you may still feel a little\nqueasy about viral genes in your food,"},{"time":510463,"text":"but consider this:"},{"time":512600,"text":"The genetically engineered papaya\ncarries just a trace amount of the virus."},{"time":519380,"text":"If you bite into an organic\nor conventional papaya"},{"time":522770,"text":"that is infected with the virus,"},{"time":525625,"text":"you will be chewing on tenfold\nmore viral protein."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530641,"text":"Now, take a look at this pest\nfeasting on an eggplant."},{"time":534593,"text":"The brown you see is frass,"},{"time":536980,"text":"what comes out\nthe back end of the insect."},{"time":540161,"text":"To control this serious pest,"},{"time":543365,"text":"which can devastate the entire\neggplant crop in Bangladesh,"},{"time":548891,"text":"Bangladeshi farmers spray insecticides"},{"time":552327,"text":"two to three times a week,"},{"time":555694,"text":"sometimes twice a day,\nwhen pest pressure is high."},{"time":560408,"text":"But we know that some insecticides\nare very harmful to human health,"},{"time":564448,"text":"especially when farmers and their families"},{"time":568035,"text":"cannot afford proper protection,\nlike these children."},{"time":572400,"text":"In less developed countries,\nit's estimated that 300,000 people"},{"time":577903,"text":"die every year because of\ninsecticide misuse and exposure."},{"time":583313,"text":"Cornell and Bangladeshi scientists\ndecided to fight this disease"},{"time":587121,"text":"using a genetic technique that builds\non an organic farming approach."},{"time":592373,"text":"Organic farmers like my husband Raoul\nspray an insecticide called B.T.,"},{"time":597263,"text":"which is based on a bacteria."},{"time":600239,"text":"This pesticide is very specific\nto caterpillar pests,"},{"time":606067,"text":"and in fact, it's nontoxic\nto humans, fish and birds."},{"time":609643,"text":"It's less toxic than table salt."},{"time":612754,"text":"But this approach\ndoes not work well in Bangladesh."},{"time":615332,"text":"That's because these insecticide sprays"},{"time":617746,"text":"are difficult to find, they're expensive,"},{"time":619999,"text":"and they don't prevent the insect\nfrom getting inside the plants."},{"time":624341,"text":"In the genetic approach, scientists\ncut the gene out of the bacteria"},{"time":627545,"text":"and insert it directly into\nthe eggplant genome."},{"time":630726,"text":"Will this work to reduce\ninsecticide sprays in Bangladesh?"},{"time":634116,"text":"Definitely."},{"time":635555,"text":"Last season, farmers reported they were\nable to reduce their insecticide use"},{"time":640106,"text":"by a huge amount, almost down to zero."},{"time":644471,"text":"They're able to harvest\nand replant for the next season."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648700,"text":"Now, I've given you a couple examples\nof how genetic engineering can be used"},{"time":652505,"text":"to fight pests and disease"},{"time":654293,"text":"and to reduce the amount of insecticides."},{"time":657033,"text":"My final example is an example"},{"time":660400,"text":"where genetic engineering\ncan be used to reduce malnutrition."},{"time":666024,"text":"In less developed countries,"},{"time":668573,"text":"500,000 children go blind every year\nbecause of lack of Vitamin A."},{"time":673239,"text":"More than half will die."},{"time":676004,"text":"For this reason, scientists supported\nby the Rockefeller Foundation"},{"time":679857,"text":"genetically engineered a golden rice"},{"time":682713,"text":"to produce beta-carotene,\nwhich is the precursor of Vitamin A."},{"time":687264,"text":"This is the same pigment\nthat we find in carrots."},{"time":690589,"text":"Researchers estimate that just one cup\nof golden rice per day"},{"time":695321,"text":"will save the lives\nof thousands of children."},{"time":699748,"text":"But golden rice is virulently opposed"},{"time":701958,"text":"by activists who are\nagainst genetic modification."},{"time":704918,"text":"Just last year,"},{"time":706528,"text":"activists invaded and destroyed\na field trial in the Philippines."},{"time":710923,"text":"When I heard about the destruction,"},{"time":713339,"text":"I wondered if they knew that they\nwere destroying much more"},{"time":717100,"text":"than a scientific research project,"},{"time":719283,"text":"that they were destroying medicines\nthat children desperately needed"},{"time":722504,"text":"to save their sight and their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725967,"text":"Some of my friends and family still worry:"},{"time":728710,"text":"How do you know genes\nin the food are safe to eat?"},{"time":731961,"text":"I explained the genetic engineering,"},{"time":733679,"text":"the process of moving\ngenes between species,"},{"time":736047,"text":"has been used for more than 40 years"},{"time":738857,"text":"in wines, in medicine,\nin plants, in cheeses."},{"time":743172,"text":"In all that time, there hasn't been\na single case of harm"},{"time":746296,"text":"to human health or the environment."},{"time":750164,"text":"But I say, look, I'm not\nasking you to believe me."},{"time":752835,"text":"Science is not a belief system."},{"time":756062,"text":"My opinion doesn't matter."},{"time":758871,"text":"Let's look at the evidence."},{"time":761681,"text":"After 20 years of careful study\nand rigorous peer review"},{"time":765187,"text":"by thousands of independent scientists,"},{"time":768229,"text":"every major scientific organization\nin the world has concluded"},{"time":772269,"text":"that the crops currently\non the market are safe to eat"},{"time":775891,"text":"and that the process\nof genetic engineering"},{"time":778143,"text":"is no more risky than older methods\nof genetic modification."},{"time":782996,"text":"These are precisely the same\norganizations that most of us trust"},{"time":786632,"text":"when it comes to other\nimportant scientific issues"},{"time":789656,"text":"such as global climate change\nor the safety of vaccines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795081,"text":"Raoul and I believe that, instead of\nworrying about the genes in our food,"},{"time":799500,"text":"we must focus on how we can help\nchildren grow up healthy."},{"time":803192,"text":"We must ask if farmers\nin rural communities can thrive,"},{"time":806327,"text":"and if everyone can afford the food."},{"time":808951,"text":"We must try to minimize\nenvironmental degradation."},{"time":812642,"text":"What scares me most about\nthe loud arguments and misinformation"},{"time":816241,"text":"about plant genetics"},{"time":817797,"text":"is that the poorest people\nwho most need the technology"},{"time":820839,"text":"may be denied access because of\nthe vague fears and prejudices"},{"time":824577,"text":"of those who have enough to eat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827804,"text":"We have a huge challenge in front of us."},{"time":830730,"text":"Let's celebrate scientific\ninnovation and use it."},{"time":834515,"text":"It's our responsibility"},{"time":836465,"text":"to do everything we can to help\nalleviate human suffering"},{"time":839902,"text":"and safeguard the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841736,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843988,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":845915,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848493,"text":"Chris Anderson: Powerfully argued."},{"time":850397,"text":"The people who argue against GMOs,"},{"time":852556,"text":"as I understand it, the core piece\ncomes from two things."},{"time":856387,"text":"One, complexity and\nunintended consequence."},{"time":859277,"text":"Nature is this incredibly complex machine."},{"time":861318,"text":"If we put out these brand new genes\nthat we've created,"},{"time":863902,"text":"that haven't been challenged\nby years of evolution,"},{"time":866326,"text":"and they started mixing up\nwith the rest of what's going on,"},{"time":869233,"text":"couldn't that trigger some kind\nof cataclysm or problem,"},{"time":872670,"text":"especially when you add in\nthe commercial incentive"},{"time":875241,"text":"that some companies have\nto put them out there?"},{"time":878794,"text":"The fear is that those incentives"},{"time":880512,"text":"mean that the decision is not made\non purely scientific grounds,"},{"time":884246,"text":"and even if it was, that there would be\nunintended consequences."},{"time":887292,"text":"How do we know that there isn't\na big risk of some unintended consequence?"},{"time":891425,"text":"Often our tinkerings with nature\ndo lead to big, unintended consequences"},{"time":895302,"text":"and chain reactions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896997,"text":"Pamela Ronald: Okay,\nso on the commercial aspects,"},{"time":899575,"text":"one thing that's really important\nto understand is that,"},{"time":902245,"text":"in the developed world,\nfarmers in the United States,"},{"time":904911,"text":"almost all farmers, whether\nthey're organic or conventional,"},{"time":907732,"text":"they buy seed produced by seed companies."},{"time":909830,"text":"So there's definitely a commercial\ninterest to sell a lot of seed,"},{"time":912932,"text":"but hopefully they're selling seed\nthat the farmers want to buy."},{"time":915935,"text":"It's different in the\nless developed world."},{"time":918196,"text":"Farmers there cannot afford the seed."},{"time":920309,"text":"These seeds are not being sold."},{"time":921935,"text":"These seeds are being distributed freely"},{"time":924303,"text":"through traditional kinds\nof certification groups,"},{"time":929365,"text":"so it is very important\nin less developed countries"},{"time":931848,"text":"that the seed be freely available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933473,"text":"CA: Wouldn't some activists say that this\nis actually part of the conspiracy?"},{"time":937097,"text":"This is the heroin strategy."},{"time":938513,"text":"You seed the stuff,\nand people have no choice"},{"time":940765,"text":"but to be hooked on these seeds forever?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":942704,"text":"PR: There are a lot of conspiracy theories\nfor sure, but it doesn't work that way."},{"time":948091,"text":"For example, the seed that's being\ndistributed, the flood-tolerant rice,"},{"time":952067,"text":"this is distributed freely"},{"time":953912,"text":"through Indian and Bangladeshi\nseed certification agencies,"},{"time":958029,"text":"so there's no commercial interest at all."},{"time":960444,"text":"The golden rice was developed through\nsupport of the Rockefeller Foundation."},{"time":964368,"text":"Again, it's being freely distributed."},{"time":966365,"text":"There are no commercial profits"},{"time":968152,"text":"in this situation."},{"time":970498,"text":"And now to address your other question\nabout, well, mixing genes,"},{"time":973771,"text":"aren't there some unintended consequences?"},{"time":976024,"text":"Absolutely -- every time\nwe do something different,"},{"time":979019,"text":"there's an unintended consequence,"},{"time":980800,"text":"but one of the points I was trying to make"},{"time":982827,"text":"is that we've been doing\nkind of crazy things to our plants,"},{"time":986159,"text":"mutagenesis using radiation\nor chemical mutagenesis."},{"time":990257,"text":"This induces thousands\nof uncharacterized mutations,"},{"time":994204,"text":"and this is even a higher risk\nof unintended consequence"},{"time":998128,"text":"than many of the modern methods."},{"time":999916,"text":"And so it's really important\nnot to use the term GMO"},{"time":1003051,"text":"because it's scientifically meaningless."},{"time":1005767,"text":"I feel it's very important to talk\nabout a specific crop"},{"time":1010109,"text":"and a specific product, and think about\nthe needs of the consumer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1013431,"text":"CA: So part of what's happening here\nis that there's a mental model"},{"time":1016608,"text":"in a lot of people that nature is nature,\nand it's pure and pristine,"},{"time":1020460,"text":"and to tinker with it is Frankensteinian."},{"time":1022697,"text":"It's making something that's pure\ndangerous in some way,"},{"time":1026343,"text":"and I think you're saying\nthat that whole model"},{"time":1028684,"text":"just misunderstands how nature is."},{"time":1030797,"text":"Nature is a much more chaotic\ninterplay of genetic changes"},{"time":1034698,"text":"that have been happening\nall the time anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036927,"text":"PR: That's absolutely true, and there's\nno such thing as pure food."},{"time":1040340,"text":"I mean, you could not spray\neggplant with insecticides"},{"time":1043397,"text":"or not genetically engineer it,\nbut then you'd be stuck eating frass."},{"time":1047500,"text":"So there's no purity there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049148,"text":"CA: Pam Ronald, thank you. \nThat was powerfully argued."},{"time":1051748,"text":"PR: Thank you very much. I appreciate it."},{"time":1053838,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}